caption: Nice Aquarium to visit with kids. The species are really good but don't expect something big. I've been to other better aquariums and I think it would be better to go to the Zoological park nearby.

A little gem in Paris XII. It's a small tropical aquarium in the city. Great for kids and adults. You can spend 1-2 hours visiting it and the temporary exhibition. Accessible for handicapped people and adapted to kids. Worth a visit.
Extraordinary time to explore the world of animals and finishes, nice decorations and introductions for all kind of creatures.
One of the best aquariums I've ever seen. Period. The staff was nice and the aquariums were obviously well cared for.  Enjoyed every moment.

Had a fantastic time! I'm always fascinated by the animal world, so exploring the marine environment was an just amazing experience. Highly recommend it, especially since entrance is free for ages 12-25

An interesting little aquarium. A good variety of fish as well as an albino crocodile. I visited because I was going to the museum on the floor above. I was slightly concerned about the size of some of the tanks, especially for the rays which didn‚Äôt have much space. There is a cafe on the floor above.

Beautiful place and ideal if you want to go with kids. You will see people of all ages there. The aquariums are full of diverse fish. The real attraction are the albonos alligators. A sight to see if you haven't. Unfortunately it was raining that day so we could not enjoy the terrace outside.

Such a fun experience! Free activity to do and relax a little, the space it‚Äôs really nice and even thought it isn‚Äôt the biggest aquarium I have been in, it‚Äôs definitely cool! Close to other nice places.
Unexpected but beautiful and exciting exploration of the under-water life. Nice tanks. A lot of fish, turtles and a crocodile. And also it is free for under 26! üôå A great one hour visit.

Great place to go to with children, seeing the animals is very easy for them and there‚Äôs steps for them to see better as well.  Access with a stroller is tedious though since only security guards can unlock the elevator. As for changing stations, only in the women‚Äôs restroom. This is an amazing aquarium with fishes and sea creatures from all around the globe! I've never seen such beautiful fishes in my life! Entry fees are free for student and really cheap for adult. I recommend it a lot!

Smaller and less spectacular than its competitor the Aquarium de Paris (no shark!) but more educational and still worth the visit. The crocodile pit is one of the main attractions. Since it‚Äôs only 3‚Ç¨ extra, take the full ticket and visit the museum. Lots of young children who were having a hell of a good time!
Very reasonable price of ‚Ç¨11 for 2 adults and 1 child. No tunnel with sharks but many different fishes, tortoises and white crocodiles. Great for families to spend an hour or two.
This is excellent for young children and adults alike. So many fish, turtles right in front of a park. Great value for money.

Cute aquarium with a lot of different types of fish. The seaweed exposition also interesting. Super appreciate it that the entrance for young people (18-25) is totally free! The water was really clean and nice that they have real corals and plants!
Is small, but a nice visit for children. They can see fishes from arround the world
I love it with all fish. I've learned a lot through the guides and they were reallyhelpful. There was an expo on Madagascar üá≤üá¨ that was about the project fishnet.
very cool!! lots of full tanks and different types of animal / fish
Amazing place I'm from Madagascar and they have a lot of fish and history from Madagascar fishes We were able to witness a live birth of turtle eggs
One of the cutest aquarium. And it's free . It's not that big but it's very peaceful. Must visit once
Nice to visit, also with young children. You can see everything in about 1.5 hours. Lots of various small tropical fish (no big ones). Has a caf√© and also a lift for wheelchair users.
Great place with many varieties of fishes. A lot of effort has been put in the description of the species. Place is a bit tiny but you get to see a lot! It‚Äôs prob the best aquarium in Paris.
Pretty nice aquarium. However, it is very small and has limited type of fishes. It took us almost two hours in line before we could enter and it took less than 1 hour to finish
It's beautiful but small. It is a nice place for kids.
What an amazing indoor place for kids to enjoy with so many different varieties and colours of fishes ! A true treat to eyes üòçü§© ‚Ä¶

This aquarium is very open, which makes is not crowded at all! The aquarium is devided in areas which represents a part of the world. The fishes and other species are extremely beautiful. Plus, there are educational panels about the endangered ecosystems. Right now, a special exhibition about seahorses is taking place!
Wonderful Aquarium that is affordable for families. Very nice outdoor set up for the summer .
nice place to visit with kids.
My favourite aquarium !! Lots of differents species in very beautiful aquariums with natural plants. And for a very reasonable price.
It is the perfect place to go with kids and have an entertaining family time. They are a lot of fishes and you can learn so much about them.
Nice but small, many interesting fishes

The biggest attraction of this aquarium is an albino crocodile, other than that the aquarium is relatively old and needs renovation. The aquarium houses fishes from all around the world. Mostly it contains small tanks with small fishes.
Great aquarium, great value for money and beautiful setting!

Small but has a big variety of tropical fish. Kids loved it. Information in both french and English.  Recommend getting the tickets online, they aren‚Äôt too strict on the time slots pre selected. We were 1hr late. You can skip the line and go straight to the entry with your email tickets.  Very clean toilets and handicap accessible. Great stop if your in the area!
An ok Aquarium. Small but good number of species
Wonderful aquarium! To be visited with children.
Staff ignorant, and enclosures weren‚Äôt open. Not 5 minutes and we were done. Won‚Äôt go back.
